rizer-google-480x480.jpg 480w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/tea-tree-hair-body-moisturizer-google-600x600.jpg 600w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/tea-tree-hair-body-moisturizer-google.jpg 1280w" sizes="(max-width: 1000px) 100vw, 1000px" /> This is one of the most important aspects of caring for your weave. Weaves also need a lot of moisture and since that cannot be provided from our scalp, we provide our weave with the moisture it needs. Adding a good hair moisturiser daily while styling will keep the hair looking great. NOTE: DO NOT USE OIL, this weighs down the hair and causes tangling. Wash your weave and wig
If you wear the weave daily, then you should wash once every three weeks. Here is how: Food for thought: Wigs have been associated with depression. A research study finds that women who wear wigs have higher self-esteem.